cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE

This paper proposes a distributed approach for training CNN-ELM models to handle big data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The approach uses MapReduce, which is a distributed computing paradigm (cs.DC). The models are trained on image data sets, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the scalability of machine learning, which could fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or neural networks (cs.NE).
